commit.message: load_669: change songname type from 'signed char' to plain char.
Fix -Wstringop-truncation warnings in load_pat.cpp

load_pat.cpp: fix several issues with processing of timidity.cfg

- skips leading whitespace
- detect bank directive
- warn on soundfont directive
- implement support for dir directive
- only appends .pat extension if isn't already there

The patch was originally authored by @rofl0r back in the day for
https://github.com/icculus/SDL_sound/issues/16.

check presence of strings.h, and include where necessary if available.

because string.h itself might not prototype strcasecmp.
load_abc: minor Watcom warning fixes.
load_pat.cpp: updated timidity.cfg paths for os/2.
MODPLUG_EXPORT support Watcom compiler.

reduce platform-dependent code usage:

- replace GlobalAllocPtr/GlobalFreePtr with calloc/free. (this
  also fixes bad use of free() in mmcmp.cpp which was added by
  PR #77 by mistake.)
- replace POSIX.1 sranrom/random with ANSI C srand/rand.
- fix wrong translation of POSIX.1 sleep() into Windows Sleep()
- remove now-unnecessary windowsx.h include
- add FIXME note about the BOOL typedef: it really must be 'int'
  but no changing it...

commit.message:
Fix MIDI issues from the fuzz-patch-1/oob_read_fixes merge.

The merge between these patches broke some important hang fixes
in fuzz-patch-1. There weren't any particularly good options for
reconciling these, but the least bad one seemed to be getting rid
of the unnecessary extra IO abstraction and moving the EOF state
flag to the mid_read_* functions.

Also fixes a -Wsign-compare warning at (former) line 1294.

commit.message:
Revert making for loop variable permanent.

- Apply less changes to original code
Merge branch 'sezero-misc-fixes'
minor tweaks to mmcmp
mmcmp.c: added a sanity check to 16bit compressed blocks' decompression

fix a minor issue PP20 depacker:

The PowerPacker 2.0 depacker could attempt to skip more than 32 bits in
a manner that results in invalid shifts. These files are now rejected.
The source of a decompilation project suggests that skip values greater
than 32 are impossible anyway.

Ported from https://github.com/libxmp/libxmp/pull/492, patch authored by
Alice Rowan.
depackers/pp20.c: fixed off-by-one source buffer boundary check.
better sanity check for num_bits
added tt_entries sanity check to mmcmp

replaced the PP20 depacker with ppdepack from libxmp:

which is originally authored by Stuart Caie and is in the public domain.
the old depacker badly decompressed a bunch of files I tested,
e.g. mod.Another_Day had 22 bytes of garbage at its beginning. New code
works just fine.
PP20 bitbuffer start ptr should exclude the 4 'efficiency' bytes.
better validation of destination buffer position and size values.

Properly validate all other destination buffer position and size values.

from modplug (openmpt) svn r3649.
